            . I watched on <placeName id="t17720715-36-crimeloc184">London Bridge</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17720715-36-crimeloc184" type="placeName" value="London Bridge"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17720715-36-crimeloc184" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17720715-36-off182 t17720715-36-crimeloc184"></join>, on the night of the 7th of July; I saw the prisoner put his hand into a gentleman's pocket; the gentleman went off directly, and I stopt the prisoner; he attempted to throw the handkerchief over the bridge, but it stuck upon the stone work.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17720715-36-person317">
                  Rebecca
                   Bowden
               <interp inst="t17720715-36-person317" type="surname" value="Bowden"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720715-36-person317" type="given" value="Rebecca"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17720715-36-person317" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was with my husband; I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief out of a gentleman's pocket; when my husband took him he attempted to throw it between the ballustrades into the Thames.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence.</p>
               <p>The handkerchief dropt out of the gentleman's pocket: I picked it up. The watchman and his wife abused me, and wanted me to deliver the handkerchief to them, which I refused, and attempted to throw it over the bridge.</p>
